node.text: @makoeats thank you
Your cooking is amazing!

Made lunch for the family with 2 dishes, stir-fry beef with Yakiniku sauce and stewed cabbage. Both will go well with rice but when I saw a bundle Mee Kia🍝 in the fridge, I just couldn't resist it because I'm a sucker for noodles!😍 I also added some Mala (麻辣)🌶 sauce on the noodles to excite my palate. Spicy numbing good!🔥😋 ⁣
⁣
My family are not big fans of noodles like me, especially when eating rice with these dishes makes more sense. Anyway, they had rice, we all had what we wanted and a happy meal.☺️👍🏻👍🏻
.
.

Looks so delish with the mee kia! 🤤
Waa
Mmm
@bonaventurefineart 😆😍👍🏻👍🏻

Lol 😂 
I think you should begin to assemble the “Makoeats Encyclopedia of Essential Asian Sauces”
I will pre-order my copy
Delish
@makoeats do you have recipe for yakiniku sauce? Or yakitori sauce? It’s also same 4 key ingredients! 😳
@kittykatrei I bought the Yakiniku sauce from @dondondonkisg
@makoeats 😂 ok I will just go buy too. I learnt how to make my own teriyaki sauce from @adamliaw he’s inspiring me to try so many things! :)

Hello we haven’t met but I am now a fan of your IG ac! Anyway I realised yakiniku and teriyaki sauce are made with the same key ingredients soya sauce, mirin, sake and sugar .... ??? So what’s the difference between yakiniku and teriyaki sauce??
@randalle22 First fry it with dried shrimp, Preserved soy bean paste and minced garlic. Add cabbage and water. Season with oyster sauce and sugar. That’s how I do it! 😄👍🏻
How do you make your stew cabbage?
Yum 😋 that looks so good 🤩
Looks delicious 🤗
Nice fusion!
@asian_appetite Yay! Same same! 🤚🏻👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻
Haha I am that “noodle” person in my family, I’ll eat them for breakfast lunch or dinner!
Noooo Carbs!!!!
This looks amazing 🤤😍wish I had some!
@makoeats oh if I go to the wet market , how to I describe this to the aunty please?
@alicialimrohner Mee Kia. If you like it thick and flat, it’s called Mee Pok.
@makoeats thank you
Hi may I know what type of noodle is this? Even better if you have the brand so I can just pick it up from the supermarket thanks!!
Amd how I get the butcher to cut the meat in such a way that I canake them into yakiniku? Tried slicing mine at home but it just doesn't taste or look as good as yours 😍
Your cooking is amazing!
